AGI - The last missing was recovered at the Suviana plant in Bargi on the Bologna Apennines. It has not yet been officially identified but it lacks the appeal only the body of Vincenzo Garzillo, 68 years of Naples. The recovery came on the fourth day of research to reinvent the workers' bodies after the explosion in the hydroelectric plant of Bargi on Lake Suviana in the Bologna Apennines. More than 200 men, including 100 firefighters, put themselves to work to search in levels -8, -9 and -10. Yesterday, in the middle of the morning, the bodies of Adriano Scandellari and Paolo Casiraghi were found. Then in the evening, around 8:00, the sixth victim: Alessandro D'Andrea. Their bodies were on plan 9.
&nbsp;
Also yesterday, the Chief Prosecutor of Bologna, Giuseppe Amato, spoke of the ongoing investigation for abrupt disaster and manslaughter, explaining that some people have already been heard and that investigations will be made on contracts and subcontracts. The entire power station will not be seized, but only plans -8 and -9 in which the accident occurred. And on the body of the victims - it has specified the prosecutor - will not be executed autopsie.&nbsp;
<h2> It was not "an instant event"</h2>
"One of the reasons why some workers were found at their workplace might be because they were engaged in emergency management." This was explained by the commander of the fire department of Bologna, Calogero Turturici, during a press conference in Camugnano on the disaster of the hydroelectric power plant in Suviana. "In any case - he added -, there were events that gave the possibility of movement to people inside the power station, not an instant event that gave no chance to try to escape. Otherwise there would be no wounded." "It is likely - he continued - that the vast majority of workers had the opportunity to move from the workplace, although not all, and made an attempt to evacuate: some managed to save themselves, others did not." Based on this scenario - he concluded - "we are doing targeted research".

